snippet.textDisplay:
Roller Coasters include an over the shoulder restraint and or lap bar. Most over shoulder restraints include a seatbelt type strap that connects to the underside of the restraint. Connected or not, it does not offer any added safety than a roller coaster without one included.

As for passing out on a roller coaster... you’re advised not to ride if you have any pre existing medical issues, it’s not the parks fault if you pass out on the ride.
